article.description: Jessica Pike scored 17 points and April Kidd and Melissa Jeltema had double-doubles to lead Oakland to a 67-51 upset over South Dakota State (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP).
article.headline: Oakland upsets No. 21 South Dakota State
article.linkText: Oakland cruises to upset of South Dakota State
article.story:
ROCHESTER, Mich. -- Jessica Pike scored 17 points and April Kidd and Melissa Jeltema had double-doubles to lead Oakland to a 67-51 upset over South Dakota State (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) on Monday night.

Kidd finished with 14 points and 11 rebounds for Oakland (11-4, 3-1 Summit), while Jeltema had 12 points and 11 rebounds.

Jennifer Warkenthein had 18 points for the Jackrabbits (14-2, 3-1) who shot 33 percent and had 18 turnovers.

The Golden Grizzlies went up 8-0 on the way to a 33-15 halftime lead. They shot 47 percent from the field in the half to South Dakota State's 22 percent and forced 12 turnovers while committing seven.

The Jackrabbits narrowed the deficit to 39-31 with 13 minutes left. South Dakota State could never make it a one-posssesion game, and Oakland got the lead back to 10 points with 2:20 left.
